title: For Sale:  Colt 1911 Extremely Rare Springfield/Remington UMC
postcontent: Up for sale is a well care for Colt 1911 Extremely Rare Springfield/Remington UMC this pistol is fully documented from 1938. It is one of the "Springfield Arsenal Suspended Serial Number Pistols" S/N 128617-133186. The frame was made by Springfield Arsenal for WW1 1911 production. However, when the production of Springfield 1903 Rifles became a priority the remaining 1911 frames were shipped to Colt. The serial numbered in the "Suspended" range were not recorded as Colt production and no records show what happened to them. This one was purchased in 1938 by my Dad and used as a combat sidearm in WW2 by an Army Officer. It was registered as his weapon and is documented. The US holster he used has a bullet hole that pierced through it. After the war he brought it home. The frame has NO MARKINGS except the S/N and US Property, which is correct. The gun shows that it was well used during the war, but, well cared for in terms of rust or pitting and has original grips i would ship upon request only to an FFL holder.

title: For Sale:  White Oak WOA A4 Service Rifle Complete Upper with CLE Kreiger Barrel
postcontent:
White Oak WOA A4 Service Rifle Complete Upper with CLE Kreiger Barrel  This is a Complete A4 Service Rifle Upper Assy from White Oak Armament WOA with a removable carry handle with a “Pinned” rear sight with ¼ x ¼ moa clicks. The handguard has a float tube and lead weight under it. It has been rebarreled with a Kreiger 1:7 from Compass Lake Engineering (CLE). The front sight is a CLE windage adjustable with the 4 screw system (as opposed to the WOA 2 screw system). I have several front sight posts and hooded rear apertures, you have your choice of sizes.   This barrel has about 2000 rounds through it probably not halfway through its competitive life. The rifling has good definition right up to the throat. Unlike cheaper button rifled barrels, Kreigers have cut rifling and last about twice as long. and I GUARANTEE it will shoot High Master scores. I retired this upper immediately after Camp Perry 2015 and have not shot it since. (I retire a upper about halfway through its life and use it as a back-up so I always have a first class back-up capable of winning.) My best at Perry 2015 was 23rd out of 1000 in the NTI (I was 7th civilian, ahead of me were 15 full time professional military target shooters). I regularly cleaned 200y and 300y rapids with this upper and shot many HM scores. I even cleaned a 600y slow prone in a practice with this.   This barrel has never seen a bronze brush, nylon only, and it has never seen any abrasive such as bore paste or any corrosive such as ammonia based cleaners, only Hoppes and Bore Tech. It is always stored with a bore wetted with Hoppes and Kriol. I paid over $600 just for the Kreiger barrel, bolt and front sight assy (see photo for receipt)! Note: The delta ring has 2 cosmetic chips, I will include a new one with the rifle.   WOA is getting about $900 for their A4 Uppers with NON-Kreiger barrels with pinned sight carry handles, and they are not in stock! WOA offers no guarantees, no proof, and no refunds. This Complete Upper Assy is proven to be accurate and reliable, guaranteed or your money back. If you are capable of winning, this upper will get you there! I have used WOA button rifled barrels in the past and many are very good (given their shorter life), but some WOA barrels are not as good new out of the box which is why I switched to the CLE Kreiger.
I can ship this, ask for a quote.  Figure $20-40 depending how far you are from NH.
